My husband brought home pork chops, so I logged in for ideas. I didn't have a lemon, scallions, or cream, so substituted pantry items--cider vinegar, garlic and whole fat plain greek yogurt. After reading the last two reviews, I mostly pan fried (and accidentally scorched) the pork, leaving only a few minutes to finish in the oven (in which I was roasting carrots, broccoli and rainbow Swiss chard to serve with it). I used around 3 tbs regular dijon, and 1/2 to 2/3 cup yogurt. I added dill to the sauce for an extra flavor, worrying that the cider vinegar alone wouldn't provide the kick of lemon juice. Result? We will definitely make it again--hopefully without scorching... The sauce is wonderful with pork, and great with vegetables, too.

