Rating: 1
There's something wrong with this recipe. There is no way that one is going to brown pork chops in a pan in the oven set to 325 degrees. The Dijonaise Sauce with Shallots has the proportions of Diijon and cream almost perfectly reversed. It overpowers the delicate flavor of the pork and the shallots become nothing but an interesting texture in the omipotent flavor of mustard. I wouldn't use this recipe again if the ingredients were free. My advice? Pan fry the pork chops over medium-high heat, about 5 minutes per side or until cooked through. Keep warm on a platter covered with foil. Saute 2 tsp flour and shallots in butter until soft, whisk in 2tbsp dijon, lemon juice, and 1/2 cup cream.

